==English==
===Noun===
'''barricade'''
# a [[barrier]] constructed across a [[road]], especially as a [[military]] [[defence]]
# an [[obstacle]], barrier or [[bulwark]]
===Transitive verb===
'''to barricade'''
# to [[close]] or [[block]] a road etc., using a barricade
# to [[keep]] someone in (or out), using a blockade, especially [[ship]]s in a [[port]]
===Translations===
*'''Noun'''
**Norwegian: barrikade
*'''Transitive verb'''
**Norwegian: barrikadere, stenge inne

